<h3><font color=brown>  <A NAME="topic01">   &sect; &nbsp;  
Entanglement between unusual partitionings of many-particle systems 
</font> </h3>


<p>

The standard usage of entanglement estimators in condensed
matter theory is through the entanglement between a
spatially connected block and the rest of the system.
Clearly, it is possible to ask about the entanglement
between other kinds of partitions of a many-particle state.
Our work demonstrates that several alternate types of
partitionings can be fruitful and instructive for
characterizing correlations in many-particle states.

